3. As for the third sinne of fornication or adulterie;
Vers. 3 have not we also such harlots as Solomon speaketh of, which say,Prov. • .18, • 9, 20. Come, let us take our fill of
love untill the morning: let us solace our selves with loves. For mine husband is not at home, he is gone a journey farre off. He hath taken a bagge of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed? Are there not amongst us too many such as Jeremy speaketh of, whichJer. 5.7. rise up in the morning like fed horses, neighing after their neighbours wives? In a word, is not fornication amongst our Gallants accounted but as a trick of youth, and whoredome made but a jest?
